                android:orientation="vertical"
                android:weightSum="5">

                <com.example.discrollview.MyTextViewHeading
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_weight="1"
                    android:padding="8dp"
                    android:text="RULES"
                    android:textAlignment="center"
                    android:textSize="18dp" />

                <com.example.discrollview.MyTextView
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_weight="4"
                    android:padding="8dp"
                    android:text="1) Team size : maximum 5 participants per team (Cross College teams are allowed) \n \n
2) All participants are requested to bring their valid school/college ID cards. Entry will not be given without it. \n \n
3) Security money : Rs 500 per team (Refundable) \n \n
4) Security money and college ID card should be submitted before the competition which would be refunded once the competition is over. \n \n
5) Only original ideas will be considered. Plagiarism of any kind (in ideas) will lead to disqualification from the final presentation. \n \n
6) Destroying any property (includes sensors,hardware material,accommodation stuff,etc. ) provided by the HACKware isn’t appreciated and it would lead to forfeiting of security money. \n \n
7) Extra time won’t be given to any team in whatsoever case. \n \n
8) If they have been assigned a certain time to present their idea then they have to be there on time otherwise it will lead to delay. \n \n
9) Although we would ensure full transparency and fair conduct. \n \n
10) Decision of organizers is final and binding.
" />

